result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler J Kollauf was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Child Sexual Exploitation-Employ,Use,Induce [Modifiers: Repeater], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.05(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:14 AM Defendant Tyler J Kollauf in court, in custody.  Attorney Eric Sheets in court for Tyler J Kollauf.  District Attorney (DA) Cass W Cousins in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Court calls the Case.
DA Cousins states the appearances.

Parties were here on Friday for a Plea Hearing and Court gives a brief review of Friday's Hearing.
Plea advisement had been given back to Atty Sheets on Friday.
Court questions Atty Sheets as to how he wishes  to proceed. 
Atty Sheets responds.
Parties did their research on the issue at hand and the parties are in agreement to what they found.
Parties are still going with the agreement that had been discussed on Friday and that it will be a joint recommendation.
Court questions again if this will be a joint recommendation; DA Cousins responds.
Court questions the defendant.

Plea Questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for defendant concurs with agreement stated.
Atty Sheets provides the plea questionnaire back to the Court.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
Count 1 - No contest 
Count 2 - Dismissed and Read In

Court questions defendant regarding plea questionnaire, waiver of constitutional rights and understandings.
Court advises defendant of elements the state must prove for the charge.
Court questions attorney for the defendant.
Court finds defendant's plea is freely, voluntarily, knowingly, and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty of Count 1:  Child Sexual Exploitation - Employ, Use, Induce 948.05(1)(a); Attempt 939.32; Repeater 939.62(1)(c).
Clerk directed to enter judgment of conviction(s) this date.
Dismissed and Read In:  Count 2 

State has complied with Victim Notification Statutes.
Victim is not present.

DA Cousins gives his sentencing arguments.
Atty Sheets gives his sentencing arguments.
Court has 3 questions for the attorney's:  Credit, ERP Eligibility and Sex Offender Registry.
Defendant does not wish to make a statement prior to sentencing.
Court questions the defendant.

BY THE COURT:
Count 1:
Determinate Prison Sentence of 10 Years - concurrent with any other sentence he is currently serving
Initial Confinement:  5 Years
Incarceration Credit:  104 days 
Not Eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Not Eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
Extended Supervision:  5 Years 
**Conditions of Extended Supervision:
Pay Costs
Pay DNA Surcharge
Participate in Sex Offender Reporting 
Recommendations to be at the discretion of the Department of Corrections
